 artistic practices. His success, she contends, was due in large part to his development of pictorial strategies—an epistolary mode of address—marked by a direct, intimate appeal to the viewer, an appeal that also acknowledged the distance and delay that defers the message before it can reach its recipient. As images, often in the form of prints, coursed through an open market, and artists lost direct control over the sale and reception of their work, Germany’s chief printmaker navigated the new terrain by creating in his images a balance between legibility and concealment, intimacy and public address.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aART / General.2bisacsh  aAlbrecht Dürer.  aGerman.  aaddress.  aaudience.  aauthor.  acommunication.  ahandwriting.  aletters.  apostal system.  aprints.  atechnology.  awriting.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z97831107109840 cprintz978022635475040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226354897423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226354897/original  a978-3-11-071098-4  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles